The direct cause of your error is that `args:` is indented farther to the right than `command:`. Assuming you want `command:` and `args:` to both be keys of the same mapping, they need to have the same indentation.

As for how to escape inner quotes in YAML, the easiest solution is **don&#39;t**. 

In your YAML you&#39;re using a **flow style sequence** (`[ â€¦ ]`) with one item, a **flow style scalar** (string) wrapped in quotes (`&#39;â€¦&#39;`). To avoid escaping issues, switch to a **block style sequence** and **literal block style scalar**:

```yaml
command: [sh, -c]
args:
  - |
    awk -F&quot;\t&quot; &#39;{print $1}&#39; ...
    sed &#39;s/&quot;//g&#39; ...
```

In the above YAML the value corresponding to the `args` key is still a sequence with a single item but it uses the block style, in which each item is preceded by `-`. The `|` indicates [**literal style**](https://yaml.org/spec/1.1/#id928806), meaning the lines that follow (and having the same or greater indentation as the first one) are all a single scalar and that line breaks should be preserved.

You can see how this YAML will be parsedâ€”and that the string&#39;s multiple lines and inner quotes are correctly preservedâ€”in the below snippet.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const yaml = `
    command: [sh, -c]
    args:
      - |
        awk -F&quot;\t&quot; &#39;{print $1}&#39; ...
        sed &#39;s/&quot;//g&#39; ...
    `;

    const data = jsyaml.safeLoad(yaml);

    console.log(data);
    console.log(data.args[0]);

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/js-yaml/3.13.1/js-yaml.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

